@startuml
title Dataflow: WebSocket Connection (Current-State)

autonumber
skinparam Style strictuml

actor "Web Client" as client
participant "WS Handler" as handler
participant "Request Processor" as req_proc
participant "JWT Manager" as jwt
participant "WebSocket UseCase" as uc
participant "Hub" as hub

client -> handler : GET /ws\n(token query or auth cookie)
activate handler
handler -> req_proc : processUpgradeRequest()
req_proc -> req_proc : bind query params
req_proc -> req_proc : fallback to auth cookie if needed
req_proc -> jwt : Verify(token)
jwt --> req_proc : user_id
req_proc --> handler : upgrade request + user_id

handler -> handler : Upgrade HTTP -> WebSocket
handler -> uc : Register(conn, user_id)
uc -> hub : register connection
uc -> client : start readPump/writePump
handler --> client : 101 Switching Protocols
deactivate handler

note right of req_proc
`project_id` is accepted in UpgradeReq,
but current hub routing is user-based.
The connection path should not imply
an enforced project-scoped subscription filter.
end note

@enduml
